=head3 Nasm::X86::Tree::findLast($tree)

Find the last key in a tree

     Parameter  Description
  1  $tree      Tree descriptor

B<Example:>


    my $N = K(key => 32);
    my $a = CreateArea;
    my $t = $a->CreateTree(length => 3);

    $N->for(sub
     {my ($i, $start, $next, $end) = @_;
      $t->put($N + $i, $N + $i);
     });

    $N->for(sub
     {my ($i, $start, $next, $end) = @_;
      $t->put($N - $i, $N - $i);
